message.content: We need to find what $10\%$ of $\$1,\!000$ is, so we calculate $$1000\times 0.1 = 100.$$Since the interest is compounded annually, the interest on the first year is $100,$ and the interest on the second year is also $100,$ and the interest on the third year is also $100.$  This makes for a total interest earned of $\boxed{\$300}.$
